Oatmeal Cookies
modified from Quaker Oats (http://www.quakeroats.com/qfb_Recipes/recipe.cfm?recipeid=474)

1/2 pound (2 sticks, or 200g) margarine or butter, softened
1 cup firmly packed brown sugar
1/2 cup granulated sugar
2 eggs
1 teaspoon vanilla
1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour
1 teaspoon baking soda
1 teaspoon ground cinnamon
1/2 teaspoon salt (optional)
3 cups Oats (quick or old fashioned, uncooked)
1 cup chocolate

to taste:
cardamom
nutmeg
etc

Heat oven to 350Â°

Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; mix well.

In large bowl, beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.

Add flour mixture.  Add oats and raisins; mix well. 

Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.

Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.

Cool 1 minute on cookie sheets; remove to wire rack. Cool completely. Store tightly covered.
